title: Sailor Brinkley-Cook flashes midriff in brown crop top and camo leggings heading to DWTS rehearsals
text:
Two celebrity contestants have now been eliminated from season 28 of ABC's Dancing With The Stars.

But the work never stops for those still in contention on the reality show competition.

On Tuesday, Sailor Brinkley-Cook, who got a surprise place on DWTS after her mother Christie Brinkley bowed out due to injury before the season premiere, was snapped heading to rehearsals.

TV gig: Sailor Brinkley-Smith, 21, headed to rehearsals for Dancing With The Stars on Tuesday flashing her midriff in a long-sleeved crop top and camo leggings

The 21-year-old celebrity offspring appeared to have a spring in her step as she smiled for the cameras while heading into the DWTS studio.

She flashed her midriff in a brown long-sleeve cropped top over a white sports bra and skintight camo leggings.

She completed her look with earrings and white trainers and carried a couple of large totes.

Got spot after mom Christie Brinkley injured: The 21-year-old celebrity offspring appeared to have a spring in her step as she smiled for the cameras while heading into the DWTS studio

Also putting on the practice shoes were actor and comedian Kel Mitchell and his pro partner Witney Carson.

Mitchell, 41, had on a khaki shirt unbuttoned over a white tank and matching khaki pants with black Velcro shoes.

Carson, 25, was dressed in a red sweatshirt and black leggings along with white athletic shoes.

Karamo Brown, 38, narrowly avoided elimination on Monday's live episode and was back at it Tuesday.

The Queer Eye personality had on a white patterned sweatshirt and navy Adidas tracksuit bottoms and trainers.

Rehearsal bound: Also putting on the practice shoes were actor and comedian Kel Mitchell, 41, left, and his pro partner Witney Carson, 25, right

Ready to dance: Queer Eye's Karamo Brown, 38, narrowly avoided elimination on Monday's live episode and was back at it Tuesday in a sweatshirt and Adidas tracksuit bottoms and trainers

On the most recent episode of DWTS, former LA Lakers pro Lamar Odom was sent home, the second contestant to be voted off the show following the departure of Mary Wilson on September 23.

Also gone is NFL star Ray lewis who announced a week ago that he was quitting the series after aggravating an old foot injury.

Dancing With The Stars airs on Mondays at 8 p.m. on ABC.
